article.headline: Akron 76, Central Michigan 69 (OT)
article.story: MOUNT PLEASANT, Mich. (AP) -- Romeo Travis scored 22 points to lead Akron to a 76-69 overtime victory over Central Michigan on Wednesday. The Zips (12-3, 5-0 Mid-American Conference) built a 21-point lead with 14:46 left. The Chippewas had runs of 10-0, 10-1 and 9-1 on their way to tie the game at 64 as Giordan Watson hit a leaner in the lane with 17 seconds left. Akron was unable to get a shot off at the buzzer and the game went into the extra period. The Chippewas (2-12, 0-6), who are shooting just 39 percent from the field this season, shot 48.3 percent in the second half. In overtime, the Chippewas never got the lead as the Zips held them to just two field goals. Travis had nine rebounds and four blocks while Nick Dials scored 16, Dru Joyce scored 11 and Cedrick Middleton added 10 for Akron. Freshman Aaron Richie led the Chippewas with 16 points, all in the second half. Sefton Barrett added 15 points, nine rebounds and three blocks. Eddie Spencer scored 14 points and had eight rebounds.
